<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>‘Peanuts’ Music Owner Sues Interior Department and 3 Companies for Copyright Infringement</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/arts/music/peanuts-music-us-government-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/arts/music/peanuts-music-us-government-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/arts/music/peanuts-music-us-government-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The owner of the “Peanuts” catalog would really like it if companies and the U.S. government stopped using its music without permission.</description><dc:creator>Aimee Ortiz</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 20:22:42 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Copyrights</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">A Charlie Brown Christmas</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Music</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Heritage Auctions</category><categor